        <body>
            <listPerson>
                <person sex="1">
                    <persName xml:id="n1"><forename>Jean</forename> <surname>Saint</surname></persName>
                    <floruit when="1925">In <date when="1925"/>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> acquired
                      manuscripts in <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1216AddisA">ʾAddis ʾAbabā</placeName> with funds from Jean Saint. 
                        The manuscripts  entered the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0003BAV">Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana</placeName> in <date when="1928"/>.
                        According to 
                        Tisserant, these were MSS. Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 110-231, but Conti Rossini states that the number of acquired
                        manuscripts was 119.
                      </floruit>
                </person>
            </listPerson>
